text: Irene van Zyl (born 27 November 1984) is a Namibian cricketer. She made her Women's Twenty20 International (WT20I) debut for the Namibia women's cricket team on 1 April 2019, against Botswana, during Botswana's tour of Namibia. In August 2019, she was named in Namibia's squad for the 2019 ICC Women's World Twenty20 Qualifier tournament in Scotland. She played in Namibia's opening match of the tournament, on 31 August 2019, against Ireland. ==References== ==External links== * Category:1984 births Category:Living people Category:Namibian women cricketers Category:Namibia women Twenty20 International cricketers Category:Place of birth missing (living people)
